 CLAUDE.md, I can see that Entire CLI manages session data and checkpoints for AI coding agents, creates shadow branches to store session metadata like transcripts and prompts, links AI session data to git commits via checkpoint IDs, and supports rewinding to previous checkpoints. So \\\"semantic reasoning layer\\\" refers to how Entire adds a layer of meaning and context on top of git's raw version control—while git tracks file changes, Entire tracks the reasoning and context behind those changes.\",\"signature\":\"\"}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":3,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":13515,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":18037,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":13515},\"output_tokens\":9,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYXaLUtc5AScEnxnHXUhD\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"7c79c1b5-2dc8-416c-a34d-4e09a0176807\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-26T23:49:21.789Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"7c79c1b5-2dc8-416c-a34d-4e09a0176807\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"0d9add88-c380-4916-83e3-d15bd655b84e\",\"version\":\"2.1.52\",\"gitBranch\":\"squash-merge-resume\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01F7Vmnf9ThPhTu1eTJS2Xjy\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Based on what this project does, \\\"semantic reasoning layer\\\" describes how Entire sits on top of git and enriches raw version control with the **meaning and context behind code changes**.\\n\\nGit tracks **what** changed (diffs, commits). Entire tracks **why** and **how** it changed — the agent conversations, user prompts, decision points, and reasoning that led to each change.\\n\\nConcretely, this means:\\n\\n**Git gives you:** \\\"file.go was modified in commit abc123\\\"\\n\\n**Entire gives you:** \\\"file.go was modified because the user asked Claude to refactor the auth system, the agent considered two approaches, chose JWT over sessions, and here's the full transcript of that reasoning — linked to this exact commit via `Entire-Checkpoint: a3b2c4d5e6f7`\\\"\\n\\nThe key pieces that make it a \\\"reasoning layer\\\":\\n\\n- **Session transcripts** (full.jsonl, prompt.txt) capture the conversational reasoning that produced code changes\\n- **Checkpoint linking** ties that reasoning bidirectionally to git commits — from a commit you can find the reasoning, from a session you can find the commits\\n- **Rewind points** let you navigate not just code history but *reasoning history* — go back to the point where the agent made a particular decision\\n- **Shadow branches** store all this without polluting the user's commit history — the semantic data lives alongside but separate from the code\\n- **Multi-agent support** means this works regardless of which AI agent (Claude Code, Gemini, OpenCode, Cursor) produced the reasoning\\n\\nSo \\\"semantic\\\" = meaning/intent behind changes, \\\"reasoning\\\" = the AI agent's thought process, \\\"layer\\\" = it augments git without replacing it. The project essentially makes AI-assisted development auditable and navigable at the level of *intent*, not just diffs.\"}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":3,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":13515,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":18037,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":13515},\"output_tokens\":9,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYXaLUtc5AScEnxnHXUhD\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"d1c7c7f4-43fd-41bc-ab8a-7b4495ff7fce\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-26T23:49:32.140Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"d1c7c7f4-43fd-41bc-ab8a-7b4495ff7fce\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"0d9add88-c380-4916-83e3-d15bd655b84e\",\"version\":\"2.1.52\",\"gi